{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Multiple Package Managers?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm ships with Node.js and works for most Angular projects out of the box. yarn and pnpm emerged to solve specific pain points \u2014 speed, determinism, and disk usage \u2014 and have since influenced npm's own improvements. All three can manage Angular workspaces; the choice is a team convention, not a technical requirement."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "npm vs yarn vs pnpm comparison"}}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm (Node Package Manager) is the default package manager bundled with every Node.js installation. Angular CLI uses it automatically unless you specify otherwise."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Characteristics"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lockfile: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "package-lock.json"}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 JSON format, versioned since npm 5"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CI install: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "npm ci"}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 strictly follows the lockfile, deletes and reinstalls node_modules"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Flat node_modules \u2014 hoists packages to the top level to deduplicate"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Workspaces"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (npm 7+) \u2014 monorepo support with linked local packages"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Essential npm Commands"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm install                    # install from package.json\nnpm ci                         # deterministic CI install\nnpm install @angular/material  # add runtime dependency\nnpm install -D @types/node     # add dev dependency\nnpm uninstall lodash           # remove a package\nnpm update rxjs                # update within semver range\nnpm outdated                   # list stale packages\nnpm audit                      # check for vulnerabilities\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm Configuration (.npmrc)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "save-exact=true          # pin exact versions (no ^ prefix)\nengine-strict=true       # fail if Node.js version doesn't match engines field\nfund=false               # silence funding messages\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yarn"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yarn was created in 2016 to address npm's then-lack of a lockfile and slow sequential installation. It comes in two flavours: Yarn Classic (v1) and Yarn Berry (v2+)."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yarn Classic vs Berry"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yarn Classic (1.x)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yarn Berry (2+)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Install model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "flat node_modules"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "node_modules or Plug'n'Play (PnP)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lockfile format"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "yarn.lock (custom)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "yarn.lock (different internal format)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Zero-installs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes (PnP \u2014 commit .yarn/cache)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Angular support"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Good"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Requires nodeLinker: node-modules"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Migration effort"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "None from npm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Medium \u2014 PnP breaks some tools"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Yarn Commands"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "yarn                            # install all dependencies\nyarn install --frozen-lockfile  # CI mode \u2014 fail if lockfile outdated\nyarn add @angular/material       # add runtime dependency\nyarn add -D @types/node          # add dev dependency\nyarn remove lodash               # remove package\nyarn upgrade rxjs                # upgrade within range\nyarn why rxjs                    # show dependency path\nyarn workspaces run build        # build all workspaces\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using Yarn with Angular CLI"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# New project\nng new my-app --package-manager=yarn\n\n# Yarn Berry with Angular \u2014 always add this config\necho 'nodeLinker: node-modules' > .yarnrc.yml\n"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Yarn Berry PnP and Angular: "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Plug'n'Play mode is incompatible with some Angular CLI internals. Always set "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "nodeLinker: node-modules"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in .yarnrc.yml when using Yarn Berry with Angular."}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm (performant npm) uses a global content-addressable store and hard-links packages into project node_modules. A package downloaded once is shared across all projects on the machine."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How pnpm's Store Works"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When you install a package, the files land in a global store at ~/.local/share/pnpm/store. Your project's node_modules contains hard-links pointing to those files. A 5 MB package in 10 projects uses 5 MB total \u2014 not 50 MB."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common pnpm Commands"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm install                      # install from lockfile\npnpm install --frozen-lockfile     # CI mode\npnpm add @angular/material         # add runtime dependency\npnpm add -D @types/node            # add dev dependency\npnpm remove lodash                 # remove package\npnpm update rxjs                   # update within range\npnpm why rxjs                      # dependency path\npnpm store prune                   # clean unused store entries\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Strict Dependency Resolution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm does not hoist packages by default. Each package can only import its own declared dependencies \u2014 importing a transitive dependency not in your own package.json throws a MODULE_NOT_FOUND error. This catches phantom-dependency bugs."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# pnpm-workspace.yaml (monorepos)\npackages:\n  - 'packages/*'\n  - 'apps/*'\n"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Angular project with pnpm\nng new my-app --package-manager=pnpm\n\n# Run script in one workspace package\npnpm --filter my-lib run build\n\n# Run script in all packages\npnpm -r run test\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Choosing a Package Manager"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scenario"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Recommendation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reason"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Solo project / quick start"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Zero setup, works with Angular CLI"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Team with npm workflows"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lowest friction; npm ci is reliable"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large monorepo"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fastest installs, least disk, strictness"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Existing yarn codebase"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yarn Classic"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Avoid migration cost"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "The most important rule: "}, {"type": "text", "text": "pick one and commit its lockfile. Never mix managers in a single project \u2014 two lockfiles mean two dependency graphs and unpredictable installs."}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Enforcing the Package Manager"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "packageManager"}, {"type": "text", "text": " field in package.json (Node.js Corepack) to declare the expected manager and version."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "json"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"packageManager\": \"pnpm@9.0.0\"\n}\n"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "corepack enable          # ships with Node.js 16.10+\npnpm install             # automatically uses pnpm 9.0.0\n"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Alternatively, a preinstall script hard-fails if the wrong tool is used:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "json"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\"\n  }\n}\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Migration Between Package Managers"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm to pnpm"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm install -g pnpm          # install pnpm\npnpm import                  # convert package-lock.json to pnpm-lock.yaml\nrm -rf node_modules package-lock.json\npnpm install                 # verify everything works\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm to Yarn"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm install -g yarn          # install yarn\nyarn install                 # generates yarn.lock from package.json\nrm package-lock.json\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Package Manager Commands Side-by-Side"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Action"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yarn"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Install all"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "npm install"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "yarn"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pnpm install"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Add dep"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "npm install pkg"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "yarn add pkg"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pnpm add pkg"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Add devDep"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "npm install -D pkg"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "yarn add -D pkg"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pnpm add -D pkg"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Remove"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "npm uninstall pkg"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "yarn remove pkg"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pnpm remove pkg"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI install"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "npm ci"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "yarn install --frozen-lockfile"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pnpm install --frozen-lockfile"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Run script"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "npm run build"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "yarn build"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pnpm run build"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why installed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "npm why pkg"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "yarn why pkg"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pnpm why pkg"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Deep Dive: npm install Algorithm"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Understanding the install algorithm helps debug dependency conflicts."}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step 1: Resolve"}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 npm reads package.json and resolves version ranges against the registry, building a dependency tree."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step 2: Fetch"}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 it downloads tarballs for all resolved packages in parallel and stores them in ~/.npm cache."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step 3: Extract"}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 tarballs are extracted and deduplicated into the flat node_modules structure."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step 4: Build"}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 postinstall/prepare lifecycle scripts run for packages that have them."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Flat node_modules Structure"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# npm hoists most packages to root level\nnode_modules/\n  @angular/core/     # direct dep\n  rxjs/              # direct dep\n  tslib/             # transitive dep hoisted to root\n\n# When two packages need DIFFERENT versions of the same dep,\n# npm nests the second version inside the requirer:\nnode_modules/\n  some-package/\n    node_modules/\n      lodash/    # lodash@3.x (needed by some-package)\n  lodash/        # lodash@4.x at root (your direct dep)\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ERESOLVE Errors"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm 7+ uses strict peer dependency resolution. If packages require conflicting peer dep versions, npm throws "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "ERESOLVE"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Resolution strategies:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Option 1: Provide the missing peer explicitly (best)\nnpm install @angular/core@18 @angular/forms@18\n\n# Option 2: Use overrides to force a transitive version\n# \"overrides\": { \"some-package\": { \"@angular/core\": \"^18.0.0\" } }\n\n# Option 3: Legacy algorithm (less strict \u2014 npm 6 behaviour)\nnpm install --legacy-peer-deps   # use only as last resort\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm Content-Addressable Store"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Virtual Store Layout"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm creates node_modules/.pnpm containing real package files. Your top-level node_modules has only your direct deps \u2014 as symlinks into the virtual store."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "node_modules/\n  .pnpm/\n    @angular+core@18.0.0/\n      node_modules/@angular/core/   # real files\n    rxjs@7.8.0/\n      node_modules/rxjs/             # real files\n  @angular/\n    core -> .pnpm/@angular+core@18.0.0/...  (symlink)\n  rxjs -> .pnpm/rxjs@7.8.0/...              (symlink)\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When pnpm Breaks Tools"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tools that scan node_modules without following symlinks may miss packages. Add to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".npmrc"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in the project root:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# .npmrc (pnpm project)\nnode-linker=hoisted            # fall back to flat layout (npm-like) for all packages\npublic-hoist-pattern[]=*babel*  # hoist selectively\npublic-hoist-pattern[]=*jest*\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Workspaces in Detail"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm Workspaces"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "json"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"name\": \"my-monorepo\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"workspaces\": [\"packages/*\", \"apps/*\"]\n}\n"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm install                             # install all\nnpm install lodash -w packages/utils    # add dep to one workspace\nnpm run build --workspace=apps/admin    # run in one workspace\nnpm run build --workspaces              # run in all workspaces\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm Workspaces"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# pnpm-workspace.yaml\npackages:\n  - 'packages/*'\n  - 'apps/*'\n"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm install                         # install all\npnpm add lodash --filter utils       # add dep to one workspace\npnpm --filter admin run build        # run in one workspace\npnpm -r run build                    # run in all (recursive)\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Workspace Dependencies"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "json"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"name\": \"@myorg/admin\",\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@myorg/utils\": \"workspace:*\"    // links to the local workspace package\n  }\n}\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI Caching"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slow CI installs are almost always a cache miss. Restore the correct cache path before running install."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# GitHub Actions \u2014 caching per manager\n\n# npm\n- uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n  with:\n    node-version: '20'\n    cache: 'npm'            # caches ~/.npm\n\n# yarn\n- uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n  with:\n    cache: 'yarn'           # caches $(yarn cache dir)\n\n# pnpm\n- uses: pnpm/action-setup@v4\n  with:\n    version: 9\n- uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n  with:\n    cache: 'pnpm'           # caches $(pnpm store path)\n"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manager"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cache dir"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI install command"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "~/.npm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "npm ci"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "yarn"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "$(yarn cache dir)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "yarn install --frozen-lockfile"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "$(pnpm store path)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pnpm install --frozen-lockfile"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Version Management with nvm and Corepack"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Managing Node.js Versions"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Different projects may require different Node.js versions. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "nvm"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Node Version Manager) lets you switch between them:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "nvm install 20            # install Node.js 20\nnvm use 20                # switch to Node.js 20\nnvm alias default 20      # set as default\necho '20' > .nvmrc        # commit required version to the repo\nnvm use                   # reads .nvmrc automatically\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Corepack for Package Manager Versions"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "packageManager"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in package.json combined with Corepack ensures every developer and CI job uses the exact same package manager version:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "json"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"packageManager\": \"pnpm@9.4.0\",   // or yarn@4.2.2 or npm@10.5.0\n  \"engines\": {\n    \"node\": \">=20.0.0\",\n    \"pnpm\": \">=9.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "corepack enable\ncorepack prepare pnpm@9.4.0 --activate\npnpm install   # automatically uses pnpm@9.4.0 regardless of globally installed version\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Pitfalls"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pitfall"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Symptom"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fix"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mixed lockfiles"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Different installs per developer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Delete all except one lockfile; reinstall"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Global CLI mismatch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ng warnings, build failures"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use local CLI via npx"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Phantom deps (pnpm)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MODULE_NOT_FOUND for transitive dep"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Add dep explicitly or enable public-hoist-pattern"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yarn Berry PnP + Angular"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Build failures, missing modules"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Set nodeLinker: node-modules in .yarnrc.yml"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm install in CI"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Flaky builds from range updates"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always use npm ci / --frozen-lockfile"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Missing pnpm-workspace.yaml"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pnpm ignores workspaces"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Add pnpm-workspace.yaml at repo root"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Security: Audit and Provenance"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Running Security Audits"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All three managers can check installed packages against vulnerability databases. Integrate audit into your CI pipeline to catch issues before they reach production."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# npm\nnpm audit                        # list all vulnerabilities\nnpm audit --audit-level=high    # fail CI only on high/critical\nnpm audit fix                   # auto-fix safe upgrades\nnpm audit fix --force           # upgrade breaking changes (test thoroughly)\n\n# yarn classic\nyarn audit\n\n# pnpm\npnpm audit\npnpm audit --audit-level=moderate\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Package Provenance (npm 9.5+)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm now supports provenance attestations \u2014 signed statements that a package was built from a specific source repository commit. You can verify a package's provenance before installing:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Check if a package has provenance\nnpm info @angular/core --json | jq .dist.attestations\n\n# Publish with provenance (from GitHub Actions)\nnpm publish --provenance   # requires OIDC token from CI\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Publishing to GitHub Packages"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GitHub Packages provides a private npm registry scoped to your GitHub organization. This is common in enterprise Angular projects for sharing internal libraries."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "json"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# .npmrc (project root)\n@myorg:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com/\n//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}\n\n# package.json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@myorg/my-lib\",\n  \"publishConfig\": {\n    \"registry\": \"https://npm.pkg.github.com\"\n  }\n}\n"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Publish from GitHub Actions\n- name: Publish to GitHub Packages\n  run: npm publish\n  env:\n    GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Installing from GitHub Packages"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Developer machine: create ~/.npmrc with token\necho \"//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=YOUR_PAT\" >> ~/.npmrc\n\n# CI: set env var (never commit tokens)\n# GITHUB_TOKEN is automatically available in Actions\nnpm ci --registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Debugging Package Manager Issues"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Verbose Logging"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# npm verbose logs (very detailed)\nnpm install --verbose\nnpm install --loglevel=silly   # maximum verbosity\n\n# Check exactly what npm resolved\nnpm install --dry-run\nnpm pack --dry-run              # files that would be published\n\n# pnpm \u2014 why a dep is in the tree\npnpm why lodash\n\n# Inspect the resolved package on disk\ncat node_modules/rxjs/package.json | jq '.version'\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Clearing State"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Full reset \u2014 guarantees a clean install\nrm -rf node_modules\n\n# npm\nnpm cache clean --force\nnpm ci\n\n# pnpm\npnpm store prune    # remove unreferenced packages from global store\npnpm install --force  # force reinstall from store\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Summary"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm, yarn, and pnpm all manage Angular dependencies from the same registry with the same package.json format. The key differences are speed, disk model, and strictness."}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "npm"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": default for Angular, use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "npm ci"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in CI, good for small to mid-size projects."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Yarn"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": fast parallel installs, mature ecosystem; Berry PnP requires extra config with Angular."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "pnpm"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": fastest for monorepos, global store saves disk, strictest dependency isolation."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Declare "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "packageManager"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in package.json and enable Corepack to enforce the version."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pick one manager per project; never mix lockfiles."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "ng new --package-manager=yarn|pnpm"}, {"type": "text", "text": " sets the manager at project creation time."}]}]}]}]}}